Problem: `ndarray` uses the following pattern:

``` Rust
pub unsafe trait Data : Sized {
    type Elem;
    ...
}
pub unsafe trait DataClone : Data {
    unsafe fn clone_with_ptr(&self, ptr: *mut Self::Elem) -> (Self, *mut Self::Elem);
}

impl<S: DataClone, D: Clone> Clone for ArrayBase<S, D> {
    fn clone(&self) -> ArrayBase<S, D> { /* snip */ }
}

impl<S: DataClone + Copy, D: Copy> Copy for ArrayBase<S, D> {}
```

~~There is an associated type, so even lattice impls won't really save us.~~

Not quite right, you could do:

``` Rust
impl<S: DataClone, D: Clone> Clone for ArrayBase<S, D> {
    fn clone(&self) -> ArrayBase<S, D> { /* snip */ }
}
impl<S: DataClone, D: Clone> Clone for ArrayBase<S, D> where Self: Copy {
    fn clone(&self) -> ArrayBase<S, D> { *self }
}
impl<S, D> Clone for ArrayBase<S, D> where Self: Copy {
    fn clone(&self) -> ArrayBase<S, D> { *self }
}

impl<S: Copy, D: Copy> Copy for ArrayBase<S,D> {}
```

